{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8960].
  {panel}

When using the Email operation to send a page as an email, currently the user lookup field is very clumsy. This is a good field to be ajaxified.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8949].
  {panel}

I find the color picker pretty hard to use. For example when I'm looking for a dark grey - I can't work out where it is.

I think it would be easier to use a hue based order. And some for greyscale.

In addition it would be nice if red resulted in {color:red} rather than {color:#ff0000} for those of us who aren't nerds :)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8936].
  {panel}

I noticed that the below page has a screenshot of search results with a second column that displays the author's name:

http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Searching+Confluence

Apparently the screenshot is from an old version of confluence and this feature doesn't exist anymore. I think this should be a configurable option and it would be useful to be able to list the author.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8907].
  {panel}

Presently there is no programmatic way to obtain an LDAP connection details inside a plugin.

We would need to write a parser with a flexible file format to accommodate for changes being made in the future.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8892].
  {panel}

We need an option in a template to add an attachment while filliing in a template. A nice to have should be that a picture should be displayed below the page, and another attachment should create an automatic link.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8891].
  {panel}

After the fill in of a template form you always return to the edit mode of a page. If you want to create a form for a user to fill in, we need to go immediately to the view mode. What we need is an extra button next to insert variables witch is a save button to immediate save the page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8889].
  {panel}

Allows the ability to customise the document such as the header and footer similar to PDF customisations.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8888].
  {panel}

Currently space pdf export allows you to choose whether or not comments are included in the export.  Page export provides no option screen, as it is a quick one-click export.  The comments are never exported by the page export.  It would be nice if they were exported when shown, and not exported when not shown.  That is, they should follow the hide comments/show comments link.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8885].
  {panel}

When users favourite a page, they receive separate email notifications for every deleted comment. If comments are bulk deleted, eg. removal of old comments, this results in an email storm. Because comment deletion is not relevant to users who favourite a page unless they are the owners of the comment, the delete comment notifications should only be sent to the comment submitter.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8874].
  {panel}

If I want to attach videos to a Confluence page, I'm forced to manually create thumbnails, attach them as well, and then work in Wiki markup mode in order to provide a an image-with-link-to-video object (can't do that in the rich text editor). A task that for an image takes 5 secs takes 2-5mins for a video.

If .wmv / .mpeg / .avi  / .mov files were natively supported by JIRA workflow would be greatly improved. If automatically creating a thumbnail image is too complicated, at least having a built-in ability to specify a thumbnail image when attaching a video object and having the "image attach" functionality support thumnailed videos, would go a long way.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8861].
  {panel}

Recently I had the requirement to give a client access to a space, but I didn't want them to see the mail archive. Currently there is no way to do this, as if you have view permission to the space, you can see all mail.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8853].
  {panel}

I need an ability for the user to e-mail to a space or page. Adding the ability to export an e-mail found under the e-mail tab would also suffice. Our Sales organization is not very computer savey and they would like to use e-mail as a means of updating their web pages.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8852].
  {panel}

I currently work on a wiki with multiple spaces (4 now, more later as we build out) and have found myself having to continually go back to the dashboard to click on a favorite page link to dig deep into another space. It would be very convenient to be able to see all my favorite pages on every page (in 'View Page' mode) in a similar manner as the 'Left Navigation Theme' displays other page options such as 'Edit' and 'Space Administration'

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8847].
  {panel}

It would be great if the upgrade process did not overwrite some customized files like atlassian-user.xml.  Simply leave the file that was already there for upgrades, as if it is the default, then it shouldn't change, and if it has been customized, it shouldn't change.  If there are changes to the schema, that's a little different and documentation of that up front should be all that's necessary.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8845].
  {panel}

I know there is a 3rd party plugin that reportly does what I'm looking for, however when I installed it, it actually crashed my server and Atlassian support said to contact the author of the plugin for help.  I'd prefer that Atlassian create this feature so from the administrator's level, I can prevent audio, video, executable and any other files I choose to block that would run automatically in a browser.  A user can simply change the file extension, but a move with a .gif extension won't start playing automatically.

Thank you.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8844].
  {panel}

I understand that I can globally change anonymous access, but here at a university, we de-centralize the space administration to the professors.  We have a policy of no anonymous write permission is allowed to spaces.  However, profs do it anyway, and the spaces get spammed very quickly and very heavily.  I understand that I can turn on CAPTCHA, but I'd prefer to be able to simply turn off the ability for anyone anonymous to edit a space and keep it that way, from the server administrator's screen.

Thank you.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8843].
  {panel}

Please do what you need to that will allow me to restore a 2.2.x backup into a 2.3.x or later install directly.  Thank you.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8834].
  {panel}

Some transactional proxies don't distinguish between readOnly methods and others -- e.g. userAccessor. We should review all out proxies to ensure that we aren't creating read/write txs when we don't need to.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8833].
  {panel}

The current WYSIWYG editor in Confluence can screw up pages, that make use of more advanced WikiText formatting. I think this is because the editor makes use of the HTML editing capability of current browsers. Because WikiText has more 'capabilities' than HTML (especially with all the advanced macros), I think it cannot always be correctly converted to HTML, without loosing information.

Wouldn't it be better to stop depending upon the HTML editing capability of browsers and instead build a specialized WikiText WYSIWYG editor? Building such editor in Flash technology could be a viable option, though you could probably also build a specialized editor with JavaScript and the DOM.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8832].
  {panel}

Use electronic templates and layouts to publish newsletters within a company with a functionality enabled to submit publishing from your desktop as well. Allow categorisation and group permissions as well as time frame for submissions.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8829].
  {panel}

Creating a space doesn't mark it as favourite, meaning it doesn't show up on the 'My' tab of the dashboard.

It seems logical that a space or personal space created by the user belongs on their 'My' tab. Therefore we should mark a space as favourite for that user when she creates it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8799].
  {panel}

It would be really nice to get "effective permissions" for users (after global, space, and "restricted pages" permissions have been evaluated)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8796].
  {panel}

We would like the ability to change the format of these messages both wording and font wise.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8776].
  {panel}

Sometimes, it'd be nice to determine if a macro is being rendered from within an existing macro.
Lets say I have:
{code}
{macro-a}
   {macro-b}
{macro-a}
{code}
What if I want {{macro-b}} to behaving differently if it is within {{macro-a}}? Right now there is no way :-(

A way of doing this is by adding a {{MacroContext}} into the {{RenderContext}}. This way I can have a look from within the {{Macro.execute()}} method:
{code}
if (renderContext.getMacroContext().getParentMacroContext() != null &&
     renderContext.getMacroContext().getParentMacroContext().getMacroName().equals("macro-a")) {
    ...
}
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
