  {panel}

A nice feature with the navmap would be to have "tool tips" when you hover over the box.  This currently is possible with a regular url.  I think it would be advantageous with the navmap macro too.

Possible solution is to pull the content within the {excerpt} tags or create a new tag which can be displayed when a user hovers over the box of a navmap.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8740].
  {panel}

One crucial aspect that is currently missing in Confluence is to export a page and all of its children into one single Word document. This makes it very cumbersome to create large documentation that needs to be exported.

Is this something that is on the list at Atlassian already?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8738].
  {panel}

This would allow better integration between Jira and Confluence.
For now the ability to link between the two applications is very limited.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8737].
  {panel}

Currently, Blogs/News being displayed under _Browse Space > News_ have the comments hidden. Clicking on the comment link, will redirect to the actual Blog posted with the comments unhide. It would be nice to be able to unhide or hide the comments under the "News" session itself.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8731].
  {panel}

It would be nice (and helpful) to have an extra field in the System Information page indicating whether the installed version is a Standalone or EAR/WAR version. It would help with Support Cases where the type of version installed relates specifically to the problem, and the question of what version is not asked until a few responses later. It could potentially speed up the whole resolution process.

It would be helpful also from a customer perspective, as they would simply need to provide the details from the System Information page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-8729].
